text: Axinaea quitensis is a species of plant in the family Melastomataceae. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist montane forests and subtropical or tropical high-altitude shrubland. ==References== Category:Endemic flora of Ecuador quitensis Category:Near threatened plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Plants described in 1934
title: Axinaea quitensis
